50|$|In 1994, the Ontario Legislature {{passed the}} “Donation of Food Act” or Good Samaritan Legislation {{releasing}} those who donate food or distribute donated food from liability {{in the event}} that an individual is affected by the consumption of that food, provided that <b>due</b> <b>diligence</b> is <b>exercised.</b> This act enabled Second Harvest Toronto to accept donations from large food corporations, helping the organization to grow substantially.|$|R
